Steps to Download and Install Kali Linux on Oracle VirtualBox

Install Oracle VirtualBox:

Go to: https://www.virtualbox.org/

Click on "Downloads".

Select your OS (Windows/Mac/Linux).

Download and install VirtualBox.

Download Kali Linux VirtualBox Image:

Go to: https://www.kali.org/get-kali/#kali-virtual-machines

Under "Virtual Machines", click on VirtualBox.

Download the .7z file (e.g., kali-linux-*.7z).

Extract the Downloaded File:

Use 7-Zip or any file extractor to unzip the .7z file.

You will get a folder containing a .vbox file and a .vdi file.

Open Kali Linux in VirtualBox:

Open Oracle VirtualBox.

Click File > Import Appliance.

Browse and select the .ova or .vbox file from the extracted folder.

Click Next, then Import.

Wait for the process to complete.

Start Kali Linux:

In VirtualBox, select Kali Linux VM.

Click Start.

Use the default username: kali and password: kali
